1. List and explain three 3 reasons why programmers write documentation. 

'Three reasons  why programmers write code is that you want to be a better writer, to let people help out, and people to use your code.'
2. In your own words, describe what a README.md document is.

It is a file that the user reads to recieve basic information and description about the desired file or project.
3. Based on what your read, what are four (4) things that should be in a README document. 
a. Information on installation.
b. A breakdown on what file or program you are about to view
c. Screenshots ans visual representaton
d. Credits,Contributions, and a manual on how to use.
4. Name and describe three (3) reasons why programmers write commmit messages when using GitHub.

A reason for why programmers write commit messages when using github is to describe the changes in the file that they made.
B. Another reason why programmers wrie commit messages is to ensure that their work is saved.
A third reason why programmers use commit messages is for themselves and others to gain knowledge over their work progress.
5. Describe three things (3) negative outcomes that could happen if a programmer has bad or no documentation.

a. With poor or no documentation, it can lead to misunderstandings in the program, file, or system that the viewer is trying to get to.
b. With bad documentaton, the viewer will find it very hard to know what the certain file does, or how to access it.
c. Without documentation, it will be difficult for a group to spread ideas, possibly causing slower development because they can't understand each other's work.